        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.) Jerome ad. Algasium, in the passage cited above, refers to these words those of Isaiah. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He shall shine, and shall not be broken, until He establish judgment on the earth: so that",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", says he, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the light of His preaching shall at length shine forth in the world, and",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [He] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "be consumed and overcome by the devices of no one, until He establish judgment on the earth, and that be fulfilled which was written, Thy will be done, as in heaven so on earth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
